+MsMathslessons //"DNA on bra clasp"//
Crime scene video -- available on YouTube -- shows this evidence being 
blatantly contaminated by the CSIs.

//"DNA on knife"//
It was her knife.

//"Simulated Break -in"//
No reason to believe that.  There were pieces of the shutter mixed in with 
pieces of the window broken *from the outside*.

//"Luminol footprints of AK +RS"//
She lived there.  It would be stranger if there *weren't* any footprints.

//"Postal police arrival time"//
Don't know what that means.

//"AK+RS with no alibis"//
Not evidence of guilt.

//"RS+AK lying to police"//
Not evidence of guilt.

//"Falsely accusing an innocent person"//
Not evidence of guilt.


You are making HUGE leaps to convince yourself that these things mean she 
must be a murderer.  Just because somebody is convicted of a crime does NOT 
mean they are actually guilty.   

The best case scenario is that the investigators were completely 
incompetent.

@Riaz 123:  Bullshit.   The Kerchers had obviously recovered enough to 
speak intelligently during this interview.   There really is no excuse for 
their sin of omission.

@James Wilson. If you're implying that because AK and RS were found 
innocent, then you haven't engaged your brain and actually looked into the 
case.
